  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Coffee Barista",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Greet and assist customers with a warm and friendly attitude, promptly attend to customers’ queries.</li>\n  <li>Prepare, plate and serve drinks and food according to recipes and quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Stay informed about menu offerings, coffee bean origins and brewing methods. Share product knowledge with customers to enhance their cafe experience.</li>\n  <li>Calibrate machines daily to maintain product standards and consistency.</li>\n  <li>Maintain a clean and organised workspace according to hygiene, safety and food handling standards.</li>\n  <li>Receive and check inventory and perishables. Monitor stock levels and replenish supplies as needed.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with other crew members to ensure smooth operations and a positive work environment.</li>\n  <li>Support the team with opening and closing tasks.</li>\n  <li>Report to Cafe Manager.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 1-2 years of experience in a cafe or F&amp;B.</li>\n  <li>Background in coffee is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Able to work well in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Able to work on weekends and public holidays.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>5 day work week</li>\n  <li>Medical claim system</li>\n  <li>14 days of annual leave (upon completion of probation period, prorated)</li>\n  <li>Individual welfare fund (upon completion of probation period, prorated)</li>\n  <li>Career progression as the brand expands</li>\n</ul>",
